On a large number of instances, the *Introduction* gadget and several gadgets on the System Dashboard does not load and displays the following error on the page: 

{quote}
This gadget cannot be displayed on your dashboard. This could be due to a licensing problem or an application error. If you need this gadget, contact your administrator for assistance. Otherwise, you can remove it from your dashboard.
{quote}

In the logs you see this:
{code}
current:@400000005766a1de152faafc 2016-06-19 13:44:52,354 http-nio-3002-exec-14 WARN rfuerst 824x19625x1 10ot3dw 104.192.142.137 /secure/admin/EditDefaultDashboard!default.jspa [c.a.g.renderer.internal.GadgetSpecFactoryImpl] Error occurred while retrieving gadget spec for
current:@400000005766a24c2ac5b30c 2016-06-19 13:46:42,717 http-nio-3002-exec-12 WARN rfuerst 826x19741x1 1hm14t5 104.192.142.137 /secure/MyJiraHome.jspa [c.a.g.renderer.internal.GadgetSpecFactoryImpl] Error occurred while retrieving gadget spec for
{code}

h2. Workaround
Restart the instance - if you are on JIRA Cloud log a ticket at https://support.atlassian.com to ask a Cloud Support Engineer to do this for you.

At present JIRA, Confluence and Bamboo Cloud are currently unavailable for some customers in Europe. The error being encountered is:

{noformat}<instance>.atlassian.net can't be reached. ERR_CONNECTION_TIMED_OUT{noformat}

Our Infrastructure and Network Engineering teams are investigating as a high priority. Further updates will be provided on this ticket.

h3. Summary

Code block text formatting is not showing correctly when using sql as a prefix is added to all quoted values
{noformat}
{code:sql}{noformat}
This affects copying the SQL code to reuse as it is not incorrect.

h3. Environment
 * Version 1000.769.1

h3. Steps to Reproduce

Using wiki markup in comments/description field, add
{noformat}
{code:sql}select * from table where column='value'{code}{noformat}
h3. Expected Results

Text formatting shows as
{noformat}
select * from table where column='value'{noformat}
h3. Actual Results
{noformat}
select * from table where column=quote">"value"{noformat}
h3. Notes:

All new and existing comments with values inside quotes and sql code formatting now have the prefix
{noformat}
quote">
{noformat}
h3. Workaround

Edit the comment and rename  \{code:sql} to \{code}
